$interpreted: : Some days later...
Beyata: "...Dear Bluebird. I've been oh so busy lately, but once these first few orders are complete, I will make haste back to Hot Spring Street to meet you."
Beyata: ...I guess it's understandable that he's busy right in the beginning.
Guesthouse Staff: Bluebird, your next guest is here.
Beyata: Alright~
Beyata: Could you please get this letter to Master Orisuke for me?
Guesthouse Staff: Another letter? The boss barely allowed you to come back to work, and now you're pushing his buttons with more letters!?
Beyata: This letter is for Master Orisuke~
Beyata: When he comes here and buys this guesthouse, he'll be your new boss and you'll have to answer to him!
Beyata: And I'll be your boss, too, so how about listening to your future boss and sending this letter!?
Beyata: Or am I wrong? Do you not agree with me?
Guesthouse Staff: Y-You're crazy! I'll send the letter, just get away from me!
: Some weeks later...
Beyata: "...Dear Bluebird, the orders keep piling in. Please wait for me a few more days..."
Beyata: I understand, I will keep waiting for you.
: Two months later...
Guesthouse Staff: Bluebird, your next guest───
Beyata: Yaaaagh!!
Beyata: Where is Master Orisuke's next letter!? It's been weeks with no word! What do you know!?!? Tell me!!
Guesthouse Staff: I haven't gotten any letters, I don't know anything!
Guesthouse Staff: W-Why don't you just ask him yourself? He's your next guest!
Beyata: Master Orisuke, you're here... You're finally here to get me, everything is coming true──
Orisuke: I-I'm so sorry, Bluebird.
Beyata: Eh? Why are you apologizing?
Orisuke: ...Your price is too high, I'll never be able to pay it.
Beyata: That's okay, I can wait a little longer for you to make more money! It is my honor to wait for you~
Orisuke: My wife... she's found out about you.
Beyata: ...You have a wife?
Orisuke: Of course... Clothier families all know each other. I was matched with a bride-to-be from a young age... I thought you would know that?
Orisuke: Anyhow, my wife doesn't want me coming here anymore, it isn't good for my reputation, and my family.
Beyata: ...I don't care about all that.
Beyata: I don't need pretty clothes, or gourmet food, or lavish trips...
Beyata: I just want you to take me away from this place.
Beyata: You promised you would, didn't you?
Orisuke: Please, forgive me! The truth is, I never had the means of taking you away from this place!
Orisuke: I was simply entranced by you, Bluebird.
Orisuke: This bag contains the money you lent me, with interest. I hope it's enough for you to forgive me.
Orisuke: I'm sorry... I'm not the knight in shining armor you envisioned.
Beyata: ...Heh~ Hehe~
Orisuke: I'm so sorry, Bluebird, I failed you!
Orisuke: Even if I can't come here anymore, I have friends who can come take care of you and─
Orisuke: ─Gyaagh!!
Orisuke: B-Bluebird... you─
Beyata: If you die, others can come and fulfil what you promised.
Beyata: Isn't that what you said? That if you died, you'd still find a way?
???: ...Buying and selling forbidden drugs right under my nose? Almost getting caught by the Alliance!?
???: If you have any other crimes to confess to, you better tell me right now.
Guesthouse Boss: Izumi! I don't, really! Please, give me another chance, I'll change! Give me a chance to clear my head!
Izumi: Clear you head? How about lose your head!
Surprised Girl: Yaaaagh!!!
Guesthouse Staff: Please, don't come any closer!
Izumi: Huh? What's going on out there?
Guesthouse Boss: H-How 'bout I go see what's going on for you, Boss?
Guesthouse Boss: Bluebird!? What are you doing!?
Izumi: ......
Izumi: (Eh, he did lose his head, after all.)
Izumi: What's your name? I like you~
Beyata: Waiting for my grandfather, for the boss...
Beyata: ...for Master Orisuke... waiting to leave this place...
Izumi: (Uh... did she not hear me?)
Beyata: Always... always waiting...
Beyata: Why don't dreams ever come true!? Why can't I ever find happiness!?
Izumi: Well, isn't that obvious?
Izumi: It's because you haven't met me, yet! Put your trust in low-lifes like them and you'll only end up in the gutter.
Beyata: ...Hehe...
Beyata: Ahahahahah!!
Izumi: Hahahahaha~
Izumi: Isn't being aggressive much better than waiting on others, alone in some room?
Izumi: If you want to hate, then hate. If you want to kill, then kill.
Izumi: ...Remember, you're Bluebird~
Izumi: You have the power to make others happy in the palm of your hand.
Beyata: ......
Beyata: (Ah... is this...)
Izumi: How 'bout I take you out of here?
Izumi: ─Let's make our dreams come true.
Izumi: Let me show you a new, better world!
